![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/e3e0a56e-64db-451e-864d-cfb0addba7a2/e385.jpg?format=original)

This week, the Major Issues Podcast heads back to Basin City to celebrate the 20th anniversary of Sin City (2005)! Join us as we break down Robert Rodriguez and Frank Miller’s groundbreaking adaptation — from its striking visual style and all-star cast to its brutal, pulpy storytelling. We explore how the film changed comic book movies, whether its anthology format still holds up, and why Marv, Dwight, and Hartigan remain unforgettable anti-heroes. Two decades later, does Sin City still pack a punch? We’ve got the answers.

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

